  <static seed="1223" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalFunctions/rationalFunctionDomain20.pg">
    <statement><p>Find the domain of the function <m>B</m> defined by <m>\displaystyle{B(x)=\frac{x - 2}{x^2+81}}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="34" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left(-\infty ,\infty \right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The only potential for an invalid input value would be if the denominator of this expression works out to <m>0</m>. However, since <m>x^2 \ge 0</m>, <m>x^2 + 81 \gt 0</m> is always true.</p>
<p>Therefore the domain is <m>{\left(-\infty ,\infty \right)}</m>.</p>
</solution>
